    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      571.87,
      543.26,
      587.41
    ],
    "text": "evidence of Puspakumara. In considering the above contention, the most important",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      595.99,
      542.95,
      611.53
    ],
    "text": "question that must be considered is whether Puspakumara is an accomplice or not.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      620.11,
      543.52,
      635.65
    ],
    "text": "Who is an accomplice? Basnayake CJ in Peiris Vs Dole 49 NLR 142 at page 143",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      644.35,
      543.43,
      659.89
    ],
    "text": "made the following observation. \u201cAn accomplice is one who is a guilty associate in",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      668.47,
      543.04,
      684.01
    ],
    "text": "crime or who sustains such relation to the criminal act that he could be charged",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      692.61,
      543.01,
      708.15
    ],
    "text": "jointly with the accused. It is, admittedly, not every participation in a crime which",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      303.29,
      38.16,
      311.31,
      49.2
    ],
    "text": "4",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      87.11,
      543.49,
      102.65
    ],
    "text": "makes a party an accomplice in it so as to require his testimony to be confirmed.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      111.23,
      546.65,
      126.77
    ],
    "text": "Basnayake CJ in the above judgment considered the following passage of the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      135.35,
      543.05,
      150.89
    ],
    "text": "judgment in the case of Emperor Vs Burn 11 Bombay Law Reports which reads as",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      159.59,
      543.61,
      175.13
    ],
    "text": "follows. \u201cNo man ought to be treated as an accomplice on mere suspicion unless he",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      183.71,
      542.97,
      199.25
    ],
    "text": "confesses that he had a conscious hand in the crime or he makes admission of the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      207.83,
      542.93,
      223.37
    ],
    "text": "facts showing that he had such a hand. If the evidence of a witness falls short of",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      231.98,
      543.01,
      247.52
    ],
    "text": "these tests, he is not an accomplice; and his testimony must be judged on principles",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      256.22,
      265.28,
      271.76
    ],
    "text": "applicable to ordinary witnesses.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      290.3,
      542.93,
      305.84
    ],
    "text": "Pushpakumara in his evidence states that he sold the water motor to Gamini",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      314.42,
      540.22,
      329.96
    ],
    "text": "Gunathilake for a sum of Rs.6000/- and gave the same amount to the accused-",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      338.66,
      543.59,
      354.2
    ],
    "text": "appellant. There is no evidence to suggest that Puspakumara knew that the water",
    "fonts": [
